applicationDomains.description:
This domain contains example events for multiple SAP object domains available for rapid PoC-in-a-box deployment and evaluation.
Each of the 5 examples is modeled as a subdomain with a different topic roots for create and change verbs.

This IFlow picks up BusinessParter change events to check for any addresses against an address validation service and republishes a checked BusinessPartner checked event.

This is a Java Springboot based CAPM application deployed on CloudFoundry.
It simulates an ERP system which produces create and change events for the following data objects : 
1. Sales Order
2. Business Partner
3. Material Master
4. Chart of Accounts
5. Notifications

Visualisation of Sales Orders that have been created.

eventVersions.description: A MaterialCreateEvent occurs when a new material object has been created in the ERP system.
A BusinessPartnerAddressCheckedEvent occurs when an existing business partner address has been validated.
Represents Sales Order related events that have been moved to the DMQ.
A Sales Order Rejected event that was enriched with a BPA workflow id.
A MaterialChangeEvent occurs when an existing material object has been updated in the ERP system.
A SalesOrderRetry event that will be fired after an exception has been processed with the Workflow Engine.
An event to indicate that an email notification for a Sales Order was sent.

A SalesOrderRejected event occurs when detected by processing through the error queue.

The message payload is unaltered from the original, and an additional attribute called {rejectedReasonCode} is added to the event topic string (note that the value of rejectedReasonCode is managed as an emumeration definition in the model).
A BusinessPartnerCreateEvent occurs when a new business partner object has been created in the ERP system.
A NotificationCreateEvent occurs when a new notification object has been created in the ERP system.
A ChartOfAccountsChangeEvent occurs when an existing chart of accounts object has been updated in the ERP system.
A LegacyEvent occurs during interaction with the modeled legacy system.
A SalesOrderCreated event occurs when a new sales order has been created in the ERP system.
A BusinessPartnerChangeEvent occurs when an existing business partner object has been updated in the ERP system.
A BusinessPartnerTransformedEvent occurs when an existing business partner object has been transformed???.
A SalesOrderChange event occurs when an existing sales order has been updated in the ERP system.
A ChartOfAccountsCreateEvent occurs when a new chart of accounts object has been created in the ERP system.
A NotificationChangeEvent occurs when an existing notification object has been updated in the ERP system.

schemaVersions.description:
**Data Structure**

TBD

Reference to standard notification data elements:
https://api.sap.com/api/OP_API_MAINTNOTIFICATION/schema


**Background**

Standard system notifications include:

M1 - Maintenance request 
M2 - Malfunction report
M3 - Activity report
S1 - Problem notification
S2 - Service request
S3 - Activity report
Q1 - Customer complaint
Q2 - Complaint against vendor
Q3 - Internal problem notification
$$ - Feedback notification
C1 - Internal claim
C2 - External claim
G0 - General notification

https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_ERP/ad9172eb200e421bb346420d437c6739/b00ec55398dd1f4be10000000a174cb4.html?version=6.03.latest

**Data Structure**

This data is structured as an array of arrays, where each element of the outer array represents an account with an associated array representing company coded budget items.

**Background**

The chart of accounts (COA) is a financial, organizational tool that provides an index of every account in an accounting system. This provides an insight into all the financial transactions of the company.  Each account is a unique record for each type of asset, liability, equity, revenue and expense.  The five types of accounts are

* Assets
* Liabilities
* Equity
* Revenue
* Expenses

https://blogs.sap.com/2020/06/30/the-chart-of-accounts-concept-sap-design-r-3-to-s-4-hana/

**Data Structure**

This data is structured as an array of partner records, each of which includes an array of address records with an effective date, and each of those contains an array of physical address records.

**Background**

The standard business partner categories are:

* *Natural person* (private individual)
* *Organization* (for example: company, department in a company, club, association)
* *Group* (for example: married couple, shared living arrangement)

It is not possible to create any other business partner categories

https://help.sap.com/docs/BS_CA/725b6ad626684262b8d74a55fc8ed089/8cae8d5377a0ec23e10000000a174cb4.html

**Data Structure**

Organized as an array of arrays, where the inner array allows for multiple representations of measurement units.

**Background**

There are 39 standard material types defined in SAP:

*Material Type / Description*
1. ABF= Waste
2. CBAU = Compatible Unit
3. CH00 = CH Contract Handling
4. CONT = Kanban Container
5. COUP = Coupons
6. DIEN = Service
7. EPA = Equipment Package
8. ERSA = Spare Parts
9. FERT = Finished Product
10. FGTR = Beverages
11. FHMI = Production Resource/Tool
12. FOOD = Foods (excl. perishables)
13. FRIP = Perishables
14. HALB = Semifinished Product
15. HAWA = Trading Goods
16. HERS = Manufacturer Part
17. HIBE = Operating supplies
18. IBAU = Maintenance assemblies
19. INTR = Intra materials
20. KMAT = Configurable materials
21. LEER = Empties
22. LEIH = Returnable packaging
23. LGUT = Empties (retail)
24. MODE = Apparel (seasonal)
25. MPO = Material Planning Object
26. NLAG = Non-stock materials
27. NOF1 = Nonfoods
28. PIPE = Pipeline materials
29. PLAN = Trading goods (planned)
30. PROC = Process materials
31. PROD = Product groups
32. ROH = Raw materials
33. UNBW = Nonvaluated materials
34. VERP = Packaging
35. VKHM = Additionals
36. VOLL = Full products
37. WERB = Product catalogs
38. WERT = Value-only materials
39. WETT = Competitor products

https://www.sapsteps.com/masterdata/sap-material-types/

**Data Structure**

A sales order object in SAP has a large number of data elements - Here are a few examples:

0CRMPCATHDR = Prod. catalog number
0BBP_POITEM = Item Number in Order Document
0CRMPAVSCHW = Material Availability Date (Requested)

This sample implementation is for demonstration purpose only, and does not implement the full object with all attributes.

The full list can be found at https://help.sap.com/saphelp_scm700_ehp02/helpdata/en/4d/aecd595deb1c36e10000000a42189b/content.htm?no_cache=true

**Background**

The sales order business object (object type BUS2032 ) is a request from a customer to a company asking for a specific quantity of materials to be delivered, or services to be rendered, on a given date.

A sales order is sent to a sales area, and this sales area is then responsible for fulfilling the contract.

https://help.sap.com/docs/SAP_S4HANA_ON-PREMISE/0f18dddf28764f5b807ecd80549044cc/6422b753128eb44ce10000000a174cb4.html
